\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b\fs28 Q-5 What do you understand by CSS opacity?\par
\fs24 Ans: - \b0 The opacity CSS property sets the opacity of an element. Opacity is the degree to which content behind an element is hidden, and is the opposite of transparency.\par
