\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b\fs28 Q-12 Who to maintain the CSS specifications?\par
\fs24 Ans: - \b0 The CSS specifications are maintained by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C).\par
\b\fs28 Q-13 What are the ways to integrate CSS as a web page?\par
\highlight2\fs24 Ans: - \cf4\b0 CSS can be added to HTML documents in 3 ways:\~\par

\pard\widctlpar\fi720\sa160\sl252\slmult1 - Inline - by using the style attribute inside HTML elements. \par
- Internal - by using a <style> element in the <head> section. \par
- External - by using a <link> element to link to an external CSS file.\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\cf1\b\fs28 Q-14 \tab What is embedded style sheets?\par
\fs24 Ans: - \b0 Embedded Stylesheet: It allows you to define styles for a particular HTML document as a whole in one place. This is done by embedding the <style></style> tags containing the CSS properties in the head of your document.\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\widctlpar\fi-360\li720\sa160\sl252\slmult1 Embedded style sheets are particularly useful of HTML documents that have unique style requirements from the rest of the documents in your project.\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b\fs28 Q-15 What are the external style sheet?\par
\fs24 Ans: - \b0 An external style sheet is a separate file with a CSS extension with all CSS style definitions for the HTML page(s). You can reference this file in the <link> tag inside the <head> in the HTML. \par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\widctlpar\fi-360\li720\sa160\sl252\slmult1 Multiple webpages can use the same link to access the stylesheet.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}The link to an external style sheet is placed within the head section of the page.\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b\fs28 Q-16 What are the advantages and disadvantages of using external style sheets?\par
\fs24 Ans: \b0 - \b\f2 The \f1 advantages of External Style Sheets are as follows:\b0\par

\pard\widctlpar\fi720\sa160\sl252\slmult1 - With the help of External Style Sheets, the styles of numerous documents can be organized from one single file.\par
- In External Style Sheets, Classes can be made for use on numerous HTML element types in many forms of the site.\par
-In complex contexts, Methods like selector and grouping can be implemented to apply styles.\par
\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b\f2 The\f1  disadvantages of External Style Sheets are as follows:\par

\pard\widctlpar\fi720\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b0 - An extra download is essential to import style information for each file.\par
- The execution of the file may be deferred till the external style sheet is loaded.\par
- While implementing style sheets, we need to test Web pages with multiple browsers in order to check compatibility issues.\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b\fs28 Q-17 What is the meaning of the CSS selector?\par
\fs24 Ans: - \b0 CSS selectors are used to select the content you want to style. Selectors are the part of CSS rule set. CSS selectors select HTML elements according to its id, class, type, attribute \b etc\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\widctlpar\fi-360\li720\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b0 A CSS selector is the first part of CSS rule. It is a pattern of elements and other terms that tell the browser which HTML elements should be selected to have the CSS property values inside the rule applied to them,\b\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\fs28 Q-18 What are the media type allowed by CSS?\par
\fs24 Ans: - \b0 The following media groups: continuous or paged. visual, audio, speech, or tactile. grid (for character grid devices), or bitmap.\par
\b\fs28 Q-19 What is rule set?\par
 \fs24 Ans: - \b0 Each (valid) declaration block is preceded by one or more comma-separated selectors, which are conditions selecting some elements of the page. A selector group and an associated declarations block, together, are called a ruleset, or often a rule.\par

